article.headline: Tennessee Tech 70, Samford 62
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Willie Jenkins scored 24 points and Tennessee Tech took over sole possession of first place in the Ohio Valley Conference with a 70-62 victory against Samford on Saturday night. Tennessee Tech (15-10, 10-4) trailed 38-26 at halftime, but the Golden Eagles opened the second half on a 16-0 run with points by six different players. Samford (14-11, 9-5) retook the lead 45-44 on a 3-pointer by J. Robert Merritt, who finished with 17 points. But Tennessee Tech put the game out of reach a few minutes later on a 9-1 run to make it 58-49 with 7:02 left off five points by Jenkins. Samford, which also got 13 points from Jon Mills, never came closer than four and Tennessee Tech made its final five free throws to seal the win.
